        <h1>Independence Palace</h1>
        <p>Also known as Reunification Palace, is an architectural work into the history of the country, was the working place of the Republic of Vietnam government during the anti-American resistance war. After the liberation, the Independence Palace was classified as a special national monument. Today, on every important anniversary of the Vietnamese people as 30/4, 2/9 thousands of people came here to visit as well as to review the history of the nation as well as the memory of the fallen heroes. because of independence.</p>

